20
00:02:22,261 --> 00:02:23,261
Wait.

21
00:02:24,221 --> 00:02:26,462
I tried really hard today.

22
00:02:26,941 --> 00:02:29,021
Did I do something to upset you?

23
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:29,583
Come on.

24
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:31,141
I think I was doing okay.

25
00:02:31,221 --> 00:02:33,022
Or was I being too slick?

26
00:02:33,381 --> 00:02:33,943
Weren't you

27
00:02:34,023 --> 00:02:35,261
just disliking me?

28
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:36,342
My personality

29
00:02:36,422 --> 00:02:37,181
is like this.

30
00:02:37,261 --> 00:02:39,381
If something occurs,
I tend to become very aggressive

31
00:02:39,381 --> 00:02:40,382
and unreasonable.

32
00:02:40,462 --> 00:02:41,022
While we still

33
00:02:41,102 --> 00:02:42,102
have not moved yet,

34
00:02:42,182 --> 00:02:43,542
you should think it over.

35
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:45,261
If you can't accept it,

36
00:02:45,701 --> 00:02:47,501
then let's think it over together

37
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:49,541
to avoid any regret in the future.

38
00:02:49,941 --> 00:02:51,501
Wait, I...

39
00:02:51,622 --> 00:02:53,462
I intended to praise you.

40
00:02:54,101 --> 00:02:54,742
Your performance

41
00:02:54,822 --> 00:02:56,022
was really great today.

42
00:02:57,221 --> 00:02:58,822
And you didn't say a word.

43
00:02:58,902 --> 00:03:00,021
I thought you were afraid

44
00:03:00,101 --> 00:03:01,261
of waking the child.

45
00:03:01,661 --> 00:03:02,742
Really?

46
00:03:03,062 --> 00:03:04,062
Really.

47
00:03:04,622 --> 00:03:06,261
That move

48
00:03:06,381 --> 00:03:07,422
you just did today

49
00:03:07,582 --> 00:03:09,062
clearly showed you've practiced.

50
00:03:09,142 --> 00:03:09,943
Next time

51
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:11,221
you hit me, go easy on me.

52
00:03:12,701 --> 00:03:13,701
Will you go up?

53
00:03:15,101 --> 00:03:16,101
Not today.

54
00:03:16,582 --> 00:03:17,782
You should also rest well.

55
00:03:17,862 --> 00:03:18,362
I still

56
00:03:18,423 --> 00:03:19,742
have to deal with work.

57
00:03:19,902 --> 00:03:21,102
When you

58
00:03:21,182 --> 00:03:21,783
are available,

59
00:03:21,863 --> 00:03:23,501
I'll come to help you pack up and move.

60
00:03:26,261 --> 00:03:27,622
Oh, one more thing.

61
00:03:30,622 --> 00:03:31,622
I almost forgot.

62
00:03:32,342 --> 00:03:34,742
(I'm a novice driver)
This thing is very important.

63
00:03:34,941 --> 00:03:35,861
Don't forget it.

64
00:03:35,941 --> 00:03:36,941
Come on.

65
00:03:37,221 --> 00:03:38,840
What do you mean by this?

66
00:03:52,632 --> 00:03:53,784
(Be kind to novice driver)

67
00:03:56,574 --> 00:04:02,168
(Be tolerant to novice driver)

68
00:04:11,774 --> 00:04:12,600
(Novice driver)

69
00:04:15,381 --> 00:04:16,381
Perfect.

70
00:04:19,102 --> 00:04:20,181
Isn't this a bit

71
00:04:20,261 --> 00:04:21,261
too much?

72
00:04:22,821 --> 00:04:23,821
By the way,

73
00:04:24,062 --> 00:04:24,662
the car key

74
00:04:24,742 --> 00:04:25,742
is here.

75
00:04:26,782 --> 00:04:27,862
Safety first.

76
00:04:28,141 --> 00:04:29,501
I'm leaving, goodbye.

77
00:04:29,941 --> 00:04:30,662
Be careful.

78
00:04:30,742 --> 00:04:31,742
Okay.

79
00:05:09,261 --> 00:05:10,662
Why are you cutting the line?

80
00:05:29,782 --> 00:05:30,741
What are you doing?

81
00:05:30,821 --> 00:05:31,622
Pay or not?

82
00:05:31,742 --> 00:05:32,382
If not,

83
00:05:32,462 --> 00:05:33,501
step aside and make space.

84
00:05:58,302 --> 00:05:59,302
Qian Hao.

85
00:05:59,901 --> 00:06:00,861
Stop right there.

86
00:06:00,941 --> 00:06:01,982
What do you want?

87
00:06:02,062 --> 00:06:02,741
You're there

88
00:06:02,821 --> 00:06:03,463
pitifully alone.

89
00:06:03,543 --> 00:06:04,662
So, I help you pay.

90
00:06:06,422 --> 00:06:07,982
Hu Xiaojiao, are you crazy?

91
00:06:08,141 --> 00:06:09,261
You got itchy hands or what?

92
00:06:09,341 --> 00:06:10,941
After Xu Kaixin hit me, you hit me.

93
00:06:10,962 --> 00:06:11,462
How come?

94
00:06:11,462 --> 00:06:12,421
I've been nice to you?

95
00:06:12,501 --> 00:06:13,501
You deserve it.

96
00:06:13,701 --> 00:06:14,821
We slapped you

97
00:06:14,901 --> 00:06:16,102
because you're a bad person.

98
00:06:16,862 --> 00:06:17,821
I don't need your pity.

99
00:06:17,901 --> 00:06:19,501
Who am I? I'm your wife.

100
00:06:19,581 --> 00:06:21,821
You should love me and not pity me.

101
00:06:22,102 --> 00:06:22,941
Be quite.

102
00:06:23,021 --> 00:06:24,021
This is a hospital.

103
00:06:24,581 --> 00:06:26,062
Did you hear it? This is a hospital.

104
00:06:26,142 --> 00:06:27,381
Too many people, no time...

105
00:06:27,581 --> 00:06:28,381
Hu Xiaojiao.

106
00:06:28,461 --> 00:06:29,261
Don't pull my tie.

107
00:06:29,461 --> 00:06:30,261
Let go.

108
00:06:30,422 --> 00:06:30,941
I said

109
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,982
I hate it when someone yanks my tie.

110
00:06:34,261 --> 00:06:35,261
Qian Hao.

111
00:06:36,141 --> 00:06:38,141
If you want to be bad to me,
then stick to it.

112
00:06:38,622 --> 00:06:39,382
Don't be nice to me

113
00:06:39,462 --> 00:06:40,462
when I want

114
00:06:40,542 --> 00:06:41,463
to give up on you.

115
00:06:41,543 --> 00:06:42,782
You make letting go difficult.

116
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:44,941
Can we not

117
00:06:45,021 --> 00:06:46,022
fight like this,

118
00:06:46,102 --> 00:06:47,381
and torment each other?

119
00:06:47,461 --> 00:06:49,941
I'm really going crazy.

120
00:06:50,742 --> 00:06:52,022
Every time I think of a divorce,

121
00:06:52,102 --> 00:06:52,783
and if I don't,

122
00:06:52,863 --> 00:06:54,302
then I'm just a fool.

123
00:06:54,501 --> 00:06:55,421
When you're nice to me,

124
00:06:55,501 --> 00:06:56,022
I wonder

125
00:06:56,102 --> 00:06:56,622
if it is

126
00:06:56,702 --> 00:06:57,982
just all temporary.

127
00:06:58,062 --> 00:06:59,022
You must love me.

128
00:06:59,102 --> 00:07:00,381
You must love me for sure.

129
00:07:00,461 --> 00:07:02,581
It's just that you don't know it.

130
00:07:02,941 --> 00:07:03,941
So, should I

131
00:07:04,021 --> 00:07:05,102
hold on a little longer?

132
00:07:05,182 --> 00:07:05,783
Then will

133
00:07:05,863 --> 00:07:07,461
our ending be different?

134
00:07:07,901 --> 00:07:08,901
But,

135
00:07:09,021 --> 00:07:10,182
I really...

136
00:07:10,341 --> 00:07:12,301
I can't hold on any longer.

137
00:07:12,381 --> 00:07:14,141
Qian Hao, I beg you.

138
00:07:14,501 --> 00:07:15,501
You...

139
00:07:15,901 --> 00:07:17,542
If you want to stab me to death,

140
00:07:17,622 --> 00:07:19,381
just stab me with one strike to the end.

141
00:07:19,701 --> 00:07:20,501
Or,

142
00:07:20,622 --> 00:07:22,501
we can forget all that,

143
00:07:22,982 --> 00:07:24,581
and be like we used to be.

144
00:07:26,302 --> 00:07:27,302
Is that okay?

145
00:07:30,422 --> 00:07:31,422
Is that okay?

146
00:07:35,581 --> 00:07:36,343
When you were

147
00:07:36,423 --> 00:07:37,662
sleeping with other men,

148
00:07:37,742 --> 00:07:38,742
did you think of me?

149
00:07:54,381 --> 00:07:55,381
What are you doing?

150
00:07:55,581 --> 00:07:56,581
Get out.

151
00:07:57,461 --> 00:07:58,461
Qian Hao.

152
00:07:59,422 --> 00:08:00,422
Qian Hao.

153
00:08:01,622 --> 00:08:02,982
I'll go back to pack my things,

154
00:08:03,062 --> 00:08:04,422
and then I'll move out.

155
00:08:05,102 --> 00:08:06,102
Don't worry.

156
00:08:06,901 --> 00:08:08,741
Even if you beg me in the future,

157
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:10,622
I won't look back.

158
00:08:11,134 --> 00:08:13,590
♪In a city♪

159
00:08:13,758 --> 00:08:16,038
♪Leave some space♪

160
00:08:16,350 --> 00:08:20,749
♪For yourself and for wonderful stories♪

161
00:08:21,054 --> 00:08:23,374
♪With an end comes a beginning♪

162
00:08:23,454 --> 00:08:25,920
♪Where there's love,
there's perseverance♪

163
00:08:26,718 --> 00:08:31,726
♪For yourself
and for countless meetings♪

164
00:08:31,806 --> 00:08:34,284
♪Having chosen stubbornness♪

165
00:08:34,558 --> 00:08:36,776
♪Don't be afraid it's not worth it♪

166
00:08:37,246 --> 00:08:41,343
♪Just consider it an adult's naivety♪

167
00:08:41,982 --> 00:08:44,127
♪With a heartfelt key♪

168
00:08:44,286 --> 00:08:47,695
♪Unlock the silent house♪

169
00:08:52,022 --> 00:08:53,022
Thank you,

170
00:08:54,382 --> 00:08:56,542
for letting me

171
00:08:56,861 --> 00:08:58,302
come to my senses.

172
00:09:27,101 --> 00:09:28,221
It's truly outrageous.

173
00:09:29,022 --> 00:09:30,022
Keep your voice down.

174
00:09:32,062 --> 00:09:33,621
Look at this child,

175
00:09:33,941 --> 00:09:34,941
who is so careless.

176
00:09:35,062 --> 00:09:36,822
He didn't even know he almost got lost,

177
00:09:36,902 --> 00:09:38,142
still having fun.

178
00:09:39,461 --> 00:09:40,941
It scares me to think about it.

179
00:09:41,262 --> 00:09:42,462
A child at this age

180
00:09:42,542 --> 00:09:44,221
can't be left unattended for a moment.

181
00:09:44,981 --> 00:09:46,621
Qian Hao is

182
00:09:46,782 --> 00:09:48,542
his biological father after all.

183
00:09:48,701 --> 00:09:50,422
How can he be so careless?

184
00:09:51,461 --> 00:09:52,461
I think

185
00:09:52,581 --> 00:09:54,422
he's just taking Xiaomi back

186
00:09:54,502 --> 00:09:55,861
for his mother

187
00:09:55,941 --> 00:09:57,221
to fulfill her wishes.

188
00:09:57,542 --> 00:10:00,062
Xiaomi is used
as a tool for filial piety.

189
00:10:00,382 --> 00:10:01,902
Getting involved with this family

190
00:10:02,062 --> 00:10:03,262
never brings good news.

191
00:10:04,022 --> 00:10:05,261
The way Heaven creates people

192
00:10:05,341 --> 00:10:06,422
is truly interesting.

193
00:10:06,821 --> 00:10:07,781
Qian Hao's humanity

194
00:10:07,861 --> 00:10:08,942
is only reflected

195
00:10:09,022 --> 00:10:10,741
on filial piety for his mother.

196
00:10:11,062 --> 00:10:12,062
I blame myself

197
00:10:12,142 --> 00:10:13,541
for never learning my lesson.

198
00:10:13,621 --> 00:10:14,942
I thought that he could make up

199
00:10:15,022 --> 00:10:15,902
for the lack

200
00:10:15,982 --> 00:10:17,342
of paternal love for the kids.

201
00:10:17,422 --> 00:10:19,221
I'm really out of my mind.

202
00:10:20,101 --> 00:10:21,101
However, I think,

203
00:10:21,382 --> 00:10:22,303
this time, Qian Hao

204
00:10:22,383 --> 00:10:24,062
will definitely not give up easily.

205
00:10:24,341 --> 00:10:26,101
We'll move immediately.

206
00:10:26,262 --> 00:10:27,462
Change Xiaomi's kindergarten.

207
00:10:27,542 --> 00:10:29,542
We'll do without his child support.

208
00:10:29,741 --> 00:10:31,461
Let's stay away from his family.

209
00:10:31,701 --> 00:10:32,701
You're right.

210
00:10:32,861 --> 00:10:33,583
After that thing,

211
00:10:33,663 --> 00:10:34,702
I finally understand

212
00:10:34,782 --> 00:10:36,182
that backing down won't help.

213
00:10:36,262 --> 00:10:37,381
He is heartless towards us.

214
00:10:37,461 --> 00:10:38,941
We must act tough too.

215
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:40,221
I've decided.

216
00:10:40,382 --> 00:10:41,182
This time,

217
00:10:41,382 --> 00:10:43,101
we must take the initiative first.

218
00:10:43,262 --> 00:10:44,461
Take the initiative?

219
00:10:44,981 --> 00:10:46,022
What's your plan?

220
00:10:50,902 --> 00:10:52,062
I haven't decided yet.

221
00:10:53,902 --> 00:10:55,621
You are bluffing.

222
00:10:56,142 --> 00:10:57,701
But losing morale is not an option.

223
00:10:58,621 --> 00:10:59,303
We

224
00:10:59,383 --> 00:11:00,821
have to show our spirit first.

225
00:11:12,581 --> 00:11:13,302
Dad.

226
00:11:13,382 --> 00:11:14,382
Chengyi,

227
00:11:14,782 --> 00:11:16,062
you should come back today.

228
00:11:16,341 --> 00:11:17,542
Come back earlier.

229
00:11:18,902 --> 00:11:19,902
Hey...

230
00:11:28,978 --> 00:11:31,672
(Mei Chengyi)

231
00:11:40,861 --> 00:11:41,861
Honey.

232
00:11:43,142 --> 00:11:43,741
Honey.

233
00:11:43,821 --> 00:11:44,821
Locked.

234
00:11:46,741 --> 00:11:48,262
Why are you shouting?

235
00:11:48,741 --> 00:11:49,542
When you see me,

236
00:11:49,622 --> 00:11:50,701
you didn't even greet me.

237
00:11:52,662 --> 00:11:53,662
Xia Chunyan,

238
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:56,021
what are you doing at my house?

239
00:11:56,101 --> 00:11:57,101
Where's my wife?

240
00:11:57,542 --> 00:11:58,382
It's up to her.

241
00:11:58,462 --> 00:11:59,982
How would I know where she went?

242
00:12:00,062 --> 00:12:00,583
Besides,

243
00:12:00,663 --> 00:12:02,461
what do you mean
by "coming to your house"?

244
00:12:02,581 --> 00:12:03,343
When buying this,

245
00:12:03,423 --> 00:12:04,942
Mom contributed money.

246
00:12:05,022 --> 00:12:06,101
So I have returned

247
00:12:06,182 --> 00:12:07,541
to my own home.

248
00:12:07,621 --> 00:12:08,941
Don't argue with me.

249
00:12:09,262 --> 00:12:10,062
We parted ways

250
00:12:10,142 --> 00:12:11,142
a while ago.

251
00:12:11,741 --> 00:12:12,382
Tell me

252
00:12:12,462 --> 00:12:13,542
where my wife went.

253
00:12:13,821 --> 00:12:15,621
She took her luggage
and went to the hotel.

254
00:12:16,542 --> 00:12:17,861
What did you do?

255
00:12:18,502 --> 00:12:20,542
You made her so upset
that she went to stay out?

256
00:12:21,422 --> 00:12:23,021
I spoke briefly to her.

257
00:12:23,101 --> 00:12:23,941
And she

258
00:12:24,022 --> 00:12:24,861
left?

259
00:12:24,941 --> 00:12:25,823
A person over fifty

260
00:12:25,903 --> 00:12:27,062
is still so stubborn.

261
00:12:27,142 --> 00:12:28,302
It's really too much.

262
00:12:28,741 --> 00:12:29,942
Who is being willful?

263
00:12:30,022 --> 00:12:31,342
You came back without a word.

264
00:12:31,422 --> 00:12:32,223
You should go now

265
00:12:32,303 --> 00:12:33,461
to take care of Xiaojiao.

266
00:12:33,581 --> 00:12:34,423
Why did you come

267
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:36,142
and make trouble here?

268
00:12:36,382 --> 00:12:37,901
I have taken care of her for a while.

269
00:12:37,981 --> 00:12:39,821
My legs and back

270
00:12:39,941 --> 00:12:40,862
are all exhausted.

271
00:12:40,942 --> 00:12:42,701
My back is killing me.

272
00:12:43,341 --> 00:12:44,501
I'm also starving.

273
00:12:44,581 --> 00:12:45,901
Can you make me something to eat?

274
00:12:45,981 --> 00:12:47,502
As a dignified president,

275
00:12:47,941 --> 00:12:49,221
I left an important meeting

276
00:12:50,022 --> 00:12:51,341
to come back and cook for you?

277
00:12:51,581 --> 00:12:53,062
Order takeout yourself.

278
00:12:53,221 --> 00:12:54,062
That's not okay.

279
00:12:54,142 --> 00:12:54,823
The oil is bad.

280
00:12:54,903 --> 00:12:56,422
It's not healthy.

281
00:12:57,302 --> 00:12:58,261
I rarely come back.

282
00:12:58,341 --> 00:13:00,221
Is it too much to ask you
to make some noodles?

283
00:13:03,941 --> 00:13:04,941
You won't do it?

284
00:13:05,621 --> 00:13:06,621
Alright then,

285
00:13:06,701 --> 00:13:08,422
I'll call Mom

286
00:13:08,741 --> 00:13:09,741
and tell her

287
00:13:10,062 --> 00:13:11,341
that you and your wife

288
00:13:11,701 --> 00:13:13,302
are teaming up to bully me.

289
00:13:14,101 --> 00:13:15,101
Chunyan,

290
00:13:15,542 --> 00:13:17,221
you know very well that Mom

